- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper deals with formal semantics and transition systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is likely because the paper introduces a new formal description technique and extends an existing language.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is likely because the paper deals with the behavior of software systems and their formal semantics.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is likely because the paper introduces a new class of timed automata and studies their properties.
- cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still possible because the paper deals with concurrency and true concurrency semantics.
